# Paths excluded from ASH (Automated Security Helper) scans.
# ASH discovers this file via get_scan_set.py and applies it as a pathspec
# before any scanner runs, so excluded paths never reach individual scanners.
#
# Syntax is gitignore-style, using **/dirname/** form to unambiguously match
# files inside the directory at any depth. Keep this list aligned with
# build-output and third-party directories.

# Dependencies
**/node_modules/**
**/.pnp/**
.pnp.js

# Build output
**/.next/**
**/out/**
**/build/**
**/dist/**
build.zip

# CDK
**/cdk.out/**

# Test / coverage / type-check caches
**/coverage/**
**/htmlcov/**
**/.tox/**
**/.hypothesis/**
**/.mypy_cache/**
**/.pytest_cache/**
**/__pycache__/**

# Compiled Python
**/*.py[cod]
**/*$py.class

# TypeScript build info
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# ASH internal outputs and logs (scanning our own scan artifacts is noise)
.ash/ash_output/**
.ash/analyze_out.txt
.ash/scan_out.txt
.ash/validate_out.txt

# Vendored static assets
# NOTE: igittigitt's IgnoreParser is invoked by ASH's get_scan_set.py with
# base_path="/", which anchors non-** patterns to the filesystem root. Patterns
# without a leading **/ therefore only match /public/cesium/... (literal root)
# and never match the actual repo path (/home/.../lib/osml-web-app/public/...).
# Always prefix directory exclusions with **/ unless you really mean "from repo
# root on disk".
**/public/cesium/**
**/public/.ignored_cesium/**
